⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Aunt Lydia
node HMT · HMT · ⟦Aunt Lydia:HMT:caa2d5⟧

WHO   — Aunt Lydia — the indoctrinator
WHAT  — The apparatus of women policing women: she manufactures consent and shame, teaching the Handmaids to accept their own conscription.
WHERE — HMT · THE HANDMAID'S TALE  Framework inputs: The Handmaid's Tale (Margaret Atwood, 1985)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a regime is most durable when the oppressed enforce it — Aunt Lydia is Gilead's genius made flesh.
HOW   — By slogans, surveillance, punishment, and a true believer's conviction that this is for the Handmaids' own good.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I teach the women to police themselves — that the cage is shelter, the leash is love; and a regime that recruits its victims as its guards need never sleep.

